name: Gray rain
description: Gray rain on the silver makes the skin turn black, bowing down a thousand times will eternally desiccate your soul. Yellow fire laces my way, burning like hellfire through you; her moves mirror my own confusion. The gray wind blows on empty air, it clings to everything, my only guide. Gray brass seethes in a fury, calling all the dead by name. Nothing speaks better than her skin, it stings and sings, and dances like a cantaloupe. Numbly she lies, she knows everything tumbles to a standstill.
